body_html: 10%, while nontrivial, is still a tenth of a order of a magnitude. As you mentioned, the binary provided by Google is still a possibility. I agree that this is an issue that needs to be solved. However it only appears to affect certain platforms. It doesn't appear to be an issue in TensorFlow itself. Please let me know if my assessment is inaccurate.
